## Concrete release sequence

When this wave actually starts, work this order:

| Phase | Effort | Outcome |
|---|---|---|
| **1 — Pre-flight** | 1-2 sessions | LICENSE, SECURITY (substantive), CONTRIBUTING, CODE_OF_CONDUCT, issue templates, real-data audit, semver tag, name-conflict check |
| **2 — Project identity foundation** | 1 session | Logo, GitHub Topics, project description, tagline.  Comparison table vs adjacent tools |
| **3 — Pre-launch quality hardening** | 2-3 sessions | Failure-mode tour; surface-compat sweep; empty-state + loading-state pass; copy-quality pass |
| **4 — Demo + sample artifacts** | 1 session | `tools/demo.<ext>`; per-scenario walkthroughs |
| **4.5 — Sanitisation tooling** | 1-2 sessions | Shared library + CLI subcommand + HTTP API endpoint.  Domain-aware via `<CORE_ABSTRACTION>` walk; `--dry-run` mode; round-trip regression-guards.  Blocks Phase 5 because `BUG_REPORTING.md` documents this as the canonical fixture-submission path |
| **5 — User-facing docs** | 2 sessions | Per-`<COMPONENT>` "what works for me?" pages; "How we test" page; "What we won't do" page; troubleshooting page; failure-mode showcase; `BUG_REPORTING.md` |
| **6 — Packaging foundation** | 1 session | Tier 1 build (Dockerfile etc.), publish workflow, Trusted Publishing for Tier 2 |
| **7 — README rewrite** | 1 session | Lead with tagline + asciinema + before/after example + matrix-honesty trust signal |
| **8 — Private beta** | `<3 weeks>` calendar | `<5 trusted users>` with the artefact and "find me bugs" mandate.  Saves the embarrassing-on-launch fire drill of "everyone hits the same bug in week one."  Cheap to set up; high return |
| **9 — Tag v0.1.0, soft launch** | Same day | Push to GitHub public, push artefact to registry |
| **10 — Hard launch** | Spread over a week | `<Show HN → primary audience platform → secondary audience platforms → blog post → conference proposals>` |
| **11 — Triage cadence** | Ongoing | `<48-hour SLA>` on bug reports; weekly fixture-import wave; quarterly versioned release |

The matrix-honesty discipline is the **distinctive feature** of this
tool.  Other tools claim accuracy; this one can prove it.  That's the
lede; everything in phases 1-7 (incl. 4.5) is the work of
communicating that lede to a skeptical audience.

